        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 5:22PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 521 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Elkins, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Elkins, Belington, Junior, and Bowden.

This includes Route 33 between mile markers 31 and 35.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
